ARTICLE 71,
THE CONSTITUTION OF THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA

6
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:30,423
THE ACTING PRESIDENT

7
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:36,054
Hi, it's Monday, March 4th,
and you're listening to TBN News Today.

8
00:01:36,137 --> 00:01:37,931
At the Korea-US FTA negotiations today,

9
00:01:38,014 --> 00:01:41,476
both parties agreed
to lower the emission standard

10
00:01:41,643 --> 00:01:46,564
of diesel cars imported from the US.

11
00:01:46,648 --> 00:01:48,066
I have something to tell you.

12
00:01:48,983 --> 00:01:52,153
About 25 to 50 thousand vehicles

13
00:01:52,237 --> 00:01:53,988
that are manufactured in the US

14
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:58,576
and in compliance
with the US safety standards

15
00:01:58,660 --> 00:02:02,247
will be imported
starting on the 20th of next month.

16
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:06,042
Although the government announced
that it was a successful negotiation,

17
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:09,129
some environmental organizations

18
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:11,339
are voicing criticism,

19
00:02:11,422 --> 00:02:14,717
saying that the EPA's
environmental impact statement

20
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,719
is excessively lower than that of Europe.

21
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:22,517
Vice ministers from the North and South
will meet at Panmunjom this afternoon.

22
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:26,646
We heard the opinions of those
at the site.

23
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:29,899
The current government...

24
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:31,067
What is it?

25
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:32,318
Well...

26
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:35,697
I have something to tell you.

27
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:36,948
Don't.

28
00:02:37,031 --> 00:02:39,200
It's been less than a year
since you got a new computer,

29
00:02:39,284 --> 00:02:41,828
six months since you got a new tablet,
and your phone...

30
00:02:42,912 --> 00:02:45,957
Don't you think you should keep it
until your contract ends?

31
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:48,751
-That's not it.
-No?

32
00:02:49,627 --> 00:02:51,838
Then go ahead and make your statement.

33
00:02:52,255 --> 00:02:54,632
I'll decide afterward
whether or not I'll show mercy.

34
00:02:55,592 --> 00:02:57,594
Loan guarantee, loan, gambling, women.

35
00:02:58,094 --> 00:02:59,596
Is it any of the above?

36
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:02,390
...air the administrative speech
to you live.

37
00:03:02,473 --> 00:03:05,268
Unprecedentedly, the ministers
of each government agency

38
00:03:05,351 --> 00:03:06,352
and cabinet members are--

39
00:03:12,108 --> 00:03:12,942
What?

40
00:03:13,943 --> 00:03:15,195
Hey...

41
00:03:19,991 --> 00:03:21,451
CHANGE IN INTER-KOREAN RELATIONS

42
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:32,128
Why are you here?

43
00:03:33,671 --> 00:03:36,299
You said Si-jin
went on a field trip today, right?

44
00:03:36,674 --> 00:03:39,802
Should we go pick her up?
Where did you say they went?

45
00:03:40,303 --> 00:03:41,971
The National Assembly.

46
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:44,849
Oh, yes. That's right.

47
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:46,643
The National Assembly...

48
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:02,533
Shouldn't you be
at the National Assembly, too?

49
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:04,369
Next to the president?

50
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:10,166
I wonder what you're doing here
next to me instead of the president.

51
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:13,920
I'll tell you.

52
00:04:14,837 --> 00:04:16,381
-Gang-yeon, I--
-No way.

53
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:19,425
Did you get fired?

54
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:22,220
Fired? Of course not.

55
00:04:34,899 --> 00:04:35,984
Are you okay, Si-wan?

56
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,571
What is going on?

57
00:05:00,591 --> 00:05:01,426
What the...

58
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:10,727
What?

59
00:05:32,498 --> 00:05:35,001
CHANGE IN INTER-KOREAN RELATIONS

60
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:55,521
Honey. Get up.

61
00:05:58,024 --> 00:06:00,026
Si-jin's teacher
isn't answering her phone.

62
00:06:01,277 --> 00:06:04,447
What about Si-jin? We have to go get her.

63
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:06,282
Honey. Si-wan.

64
00:07:13,224 --> 00:07:14,892
Hurry! This way!

65
00:07:37,623 --> 00:07:41,502
DAY 60: THE ACTING PRESIDENT
EPISODE 1

66
00:08:18,372 --> 00:08:22,084
THE DAY OF THE ATTACK, 9 A.M.

67
00:08:29,258 --> 00:08:32,428
Safety and security,
the VIP's travel route, check.

68
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:35,056
The top center section is good to go.

69
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:37,517
Okay, good.

70
00:08:38,976 --> 00:08:41,145
CHIEF SECRETARY OF PRESIDENTIAL PROTOCOL
CHOE HO-JEON

71
00:08:49,987 --> 00:08:53,074
PROTOCOL ADMINISTRATOR
PARK SU-GYO

72
00:08:53,157 --> 00:08:55,952
Isn't the president greeting people

73
00:08:56,536 --> 00:09:00,456
from 1, 2, 3 steps away

74
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:02,291
from the podium?

75
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:04,877
Listen, Mr. Park.

76
00:09:05,419 --> 00:09:09,465
Are you trying to win a medal
for saving costs by using less tape?

77
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:12,843
The quick-tempered president
will be excited

78
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:15,096
and will pass right by it
unless it stands out.

79
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:16,764
Know what will happen then?

80
00:09:17,932 --> 00:09:20,268
The opposing parties will come together

81
00:09:20,351 --> 00:09:22,144
and have a ball.

82
00:09:22,436 --> 00:09:25,064
They'll say the president
belittled the National Assembly

83
00:09:25,147 --> 00:09:26,315
and that he has no class.

84
00:09:26,607 --> 00:09:28,359
The newspapers will sing

85
00:09:28,442 --> 00:09:30,403
and internet sites
will play accompaniment.

86
00:09:30,695 --> 00:09:32,572
It's not even the World Cup,

87
00:09:32,655 --> 00:09:35,491
but the whole nation
will come together as one.

88
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:39,412
How long has it been
since you worked at the Blue House?

89
00:09:39,996 --> 00:09:44,041
It's been a year since I came to
the Blue House and served the president.

90
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:45,710
Su-gyo.

91
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:49,005
Being a protocol administrator

92
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:52,133
isn't about serving things
to the president on a silver platter.

93
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:54,969
You have to be more like a traffic light.

94
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:57,054
A traffic light?

95
00:09:57,138 --> 00:09:58,431
Stop or go.

96
00:09:58,514 --> 00:10:00,808
Front or back. Left or right.

97
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:03,728
You signal everyone,

98
00:10:04,812 --> 00:10:07,982
so the superiors
don't crash into each other.

99
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:10,901
It isn't that difficult.

100
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:15,448
If you save tape and cause our leader's
approval rating to drop,

101
00:10:15,906 --> 00:10:18,451
it'll be on your shoulders.

102
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:22,580
-Is everything okay?
-Yes.

103
00:10:22,663 --> 00:10:23,914
Let's go.

104
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,626
Let's pick up our leader.

105
00:10:48,606 --> 00:10:50,358
CURRENT ECONOMIC TREND

106
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:51,400
SPEECH

107
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:54,820
PRESIDENT
YANG JIN-MAN

108
00:10:54,904 --> 00:10:57,615
Mr. President, Secretary Choe called.

109
00:10:57,698 --> 00:10:59,992
The vehicles
and the National Assembly are clear.

110
00:11:00,242 --> 00:11:02,286
You can leave as soon as you're ready.

111
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,877
Here is the approval rating

112
00:11:10,586 --> 00:11:12,588
of the government administration
as of yesterday.

113
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:23,349
APPROVAL RATING

114
00:11:23,432 --> 00:11:25,685
GOVERNMENT ADMINISTRATION EVALUATION

115
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:32,525
Do you know

116
00:11:33,275 --> 00:11:34,735
who the easiest man

117
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:36,821
in the world is?

118
00:11:39,115 --> 00:11:40,116
No, I don't.

119
00:11:41,742 --> 00:11:43,536
One thing for sure is that it isn't me.

120
00:11:47,331 --> 00:11:49,875
Who is the easiest man?

121
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:53,421
A president with a single-digit
approval rating.

122
00:11:55,047 --> 00:11:58,008
If someone holds out a hand,
regardless of who they might be,

123
00:11:58,592 --> 00:12:00,469
he'd be willing to give up his soul.

124
00:12:03,931 --> 00:12:05,057
Goodness, you guys.

125
00:12:05,641 --> 00:12:07,309
Smile a little.

126
00:12:07,893 --> 00:12:09,228
I'm not talking about myself.

127
00:12:09,937 --> 00:12:12,940
It's a joke the Prime Minister of France

128
00:12:13,023 --> 00:12:15,651
told me during the G20 Banquet.

129
00:12:15,901 --> 00:12:16,736
It's a joke.

130
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:20,322
I'm ashamed, Mr. President.

131
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:23,576
Gang-ho.

132
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,035
Yes?

133
00:12:29,749 --> 00:12:33,085
You can still provide for your family
even if you leave the Blue House, right?

134
00:12:33,794 --> 00:12:34,670
Pardon?

135
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:36,005
Today,

136
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:38,215
after the State of the Nation Address,

137
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:41,135
if there seems to be
no chance for a rebound,

138
00:12:42,178 --> 00:12:45,556
let's stop worrying about polls
and approval ratings.

139
00:12:46,682 --> 00:12:47,767
I'm a failure anyway.

140
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:50,853
What good would checking numbers
every morning do me?

141
00:12:51,896 --> 00:12:53,564
You'd just be embarrassed,

142
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:56,692
and I'd be shameless.

143
00:12:59,653 --> 00:13:01,947
-But Mr. President--
-Secretary Cha.

144
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:06,118
Isn't it almost time to leave?

145
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:07,703
Yes, sir.

146
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:25,346
Is something wrong?

147
00:13:25,429 --> 00:13:26,430
Give me a minute.

148
00:13:26,514 --> 00:13:29,391
STATE MINISTER OF POLITICAL AFFAIRS
SIN SEONG-JUN

149
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:30,768
I heard something shocking

150
00:13:31,268 --> 00:13:33,604
will be shared during the speech.
You know what it is, right?

151
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:36,941
Let's hear what the hidden card is.

152
00:13:37,024 --> 00:13:39,485
If you and I both knew,
it wouldn't be a hidden card,

153
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:42,988
but an obvious card.
I don't know what it is.

154
00:13:43,572 --> 00:13:45,699
Come on. We both know you're lying.

155
00:13:46,325 --> 00:13:48,661
Let's ask the administrator
of the Speechwriting Office

156
00:13:48,786 --> 00:13:51,080
for a copy of the speech.

157
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:53,833
I'm
the state minister of political affairs.

158
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:57,169
It's my responsibility to mediate between
the Assembly and the Blue House.

159
00:13:57,878 --> 00:14:00,881
The guys in the opposing parties
need something to choose sides.

160
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:03,259
Whether the fight be indoors or out.

161
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:06,387
The sun is harsh right now.

162
00:14:06,470 --> 00:14:08,556
You don't want to be out there.

163
00:14:09,139 --> 00:14:10,516
What do you think?

164
00:14:10,808 --> 00:14:12,768
Should I have them buy sunscreen?

165
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:14,103
Should I?

166
00:14:15,521 --> 00:14:19,525
You must be more worried
about the opposing party's assemblymen

167
00:14:19,608 --> 00:14:21,068
than the president.

168
00:14:21,652 --> 00:14:23,195
No, not really.

169
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:25,447
It isn't about the parties.

170
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:27,867
We're all partners
in government administration.

171
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:36,792
Is this the Speechwriting Office?

172
00:14:37,793 --> 00:14:41,213
The script for today's
State of the Nation Address...

173
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:42,965
Yes.

174
00:14:44,008 --> 00:14:46,051
Could you have

175
00:14:46,176 --> 00:14:48,721
everyone and their mothers
talking about it already?

176
00:14:49,471 --> 00:14:50,598
If you need to change buses,

177
00:14:50,681 --> 00:14:52,725
buy a bus ticket with your own money.

178
00:14:52,808 --> 00:14:55,311
Don't try to use the president's name
to secure a spot.

179
00:14:56,395 --> 00:14:57,771
Yes, have a good day.

180
00:15:01,191 --> 00:15:04,904
You think you're a founding contributor
of this administration, don't you?

181
00:15:06,488 --> 00:15:07,698
Your career

182
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:10,075
ends with him.

183
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,953
He hasn't served half his term yet,

184
00:15:13,037 --> 00:15:14,997
but he has a single-digit approval rating.

185
00:15:16,165 --> 00:15:17,583
This ship is going down.

186
00:15:19,126 --> 00:15:22,212
Start rowing, and row hard.

187
00:15:22,338 --> 00:15:24,465
You have strong arms.

188
00:15:24,798 --> 00:15:26,926
One, two. One, two.

189
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:39,813
Do you think North Korea will agree
to our requests by the end?

190
00:15:40,731 --> 00:15:43,192
We need to settle on a peace treaty

191
00:15:43,275 --> 00:15:46,195
within the year no matter what it takes.

192
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:49,573
Only then will we be free
from the attack of the opposing party.

193
00:15:49,657 --> 00:15:51,742
If North Korea-United States relations
get resolved,

194
00:15:52,576 --> 00:15:54,119
I doubt North Korea will slow down.

195
00:15:54,203 --> 00:15:58,332
We can't let the American radicals
lead public opinion.

196
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:03,504
President Reynold must need something
to show his people.

197
00:16:03,587 --> 00:16:05,756
The midterm elections are coming up.

198
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:09,760
The US has made

199
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:13,430
some unreasonable requests
for the FTA renegotiations.

200
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:16,558
They must know we're in no place

201
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:19,144
to turn it down.

202
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:21,438
He sells arms

203
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:23,315
and peace.

204
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:28,153
President Reynold
is quite the natural-born businessman.

205
00:16:30,197 --> 00:16:31,031
Secretary Han.

206
00:16:32,449 --> 00:16:34,034
What do you think?

207
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:36,453
Do you think

208
00:16:36,829 --> 00:16:39,832
I still have a chance left?

209
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:41,375
Or...

210
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:49,591
Please bring the president
a warm cup of tea.

211
00:16:50,592 --> 00:16:53,595
You've done a good job thus far.

212
00:16:54,805 --> 00:16:56,557
A historian said

213
00:16:56,640 --> 00:16:59,143
that ever since Noron ruled
during the Joseon Dynasty,

214
00:16:59,226 --> 00:17:01,687
President Yang Jin-man's administration
was the first

215
00:17:02,229 --> 00:17:04,273
to succeed in the change of regime.

216
00:17:22,082 --> 00:17:22,958
So?

217
00:17:24,293 --> 00:17:26,003
Am I supposed to be satisfied

218
00:17:26,086 --> 00:17:28,505
with my title as the president
that succeeded in regime change

219
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:31,759
and sit here doing nothing
but securing my seat

220
00:17:32,384 --> 00:17:34,219
for the rest of my term?

221
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:36,013
Is that it?

222
00:17:36,972 --> 00:17:37,973
Is it?

223
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:44,646
I wanted to change history,
not just the government!

224
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,106
What I want...

225
00:17:48,025 --> 00:17:50,444
is for you to stop getting hurt.

226
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:55,407
Whether you change the nation or history,

227
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:57,326
do as you please.

228
00:17:58,243 --> 00:18:02,331
However, you can't force me to think
that there is anything more important

229
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:04,875
than you, Mr. President.

230
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:13,217
You don't have to worry
about the FTA renegotiations.

231
00:18:14,259 --> 00:18:15,427
I've sent one of our people

232
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:17,429
to ensure our alliance
with the US won't suffer.

233
00:18:22,643 --> 00:18:24,269
These are the president's wishes.

234
00:18:25,312 --> 00:18:26,313
Okay.

235
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:32,736
I'll have to ask for your cooperation.

236
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:36,657
ENVIRONMENTAL EFFECTS EVALUATION

237
00:18:43,205 --> 00:18:45,290
CHIEF OF ECONOMIC AFFAIRS
GU YONG-WAN

238
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:47,835
The US negotiating team
contacted us yesterday.

239
00:18:48,127 --> 00:18:50,129
They asked us to lower
the environmental standards

240
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:51,672
for vehicles from the US

241
00:18:52,256 --> 00:18:55,884
to fit the standards of the US, not Korea.

242
00:18:56,009 --> 00:19:00,180
The number of imported cars
will go up to 50,000 instead of 25.

243
00:19:00,347 --> 00:19:03,392
However, I have attached the EPA's
environmental impact statement

244
00:19:03,475 --> 00:19:06,311
which shows that the air pollution level
is very low,

245
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:08,063
as you can see.

246
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:13,318
I know, I know.

247
00:19:13,902 --> 00:19:16,613
It's true. It's much lower

248
00:19:16,697 --> 00:19:18,866
than Korea's emission control standard.

249
00:19:19,449 --> 00:19:22,035
Of course the degree of air pollution

250
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:23,787
and fine dust will rise.

251
00:19:24,955 --> 00:19:26,540
But what can we do?

252
00:19:27,124 --> 00:19:28,750
We're dealing with the US.

253
00:19:32,504 --> 00:19:33,839
When you encounter a tiger,

254
00:19:34,131 --> 00:19:36,717
it's best to throw snacks its way.

255
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:38,552
Minister Park.

256
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:44,391
We can't let it rip our limbs off, right?
We have kids to feed at home.

257
00:19:46,810 --> 00:19:48,020
Minister Park,

258
00:19:48,729 --> 00:19:50,147
are you even listening to us?

259
00:20:00,616 --> 00:20:02,117
MINISTER OF ENVIRONMENT
PARK MU-JIN

260
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:03,702
A contaminated plastic bottle

261
00:20:04,411 --> 00:20:06,788
is no longer recyclable.
It's just regular garbage

