such complex jargon?

467
00:37:14,857 --> 00:37:17,109
"Do you know what science
and politics have in common?"

468
00:37:18,069 --> 00:37:21,113
That's what you asked me
the first day we met.

469
00:37:23,074 --> 00:37:24,283
You told me the answer.

470
00:37:25,326 --> 00:37:27,245
"In both fields,
it's hard to say who's lying."

471
00:37:31,415 --> 00:37:32,541
That answer

472
00:37:33,042 --> 00:37:35,211
is what made me cast my vote for you.

473
00:37:36,087 --> 00:37:38,839
Because you were a good person
whom I could trust.

474
00:37:41,342 --> 00:37:42,551
But now,

475
00:37:43,886 --> 00:37:45,805
you're telling me to lie,

476
00:37:47,807 --> 00:37:48,975
to feign mercy

477
00:37:49,934 --> 00:37:50,935
and generosity.

478
00:37:55,606 --> 00:37:56,482
Minister Park,

479
00:37:57,441 --> 00:38:00,027
you do not know politics.

480
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:02,780
"You may not know politics,
but I'll let you argue policies."

481
00:38:04,407 --> 00:38:06,701
It's what you promised me

482
00:38:07,493 --> 00:38:08,327
that very day.

483
00:38:12,373 --> 00:38:13,666
Then I'll make another one.

484
00:38:14,208 --> 00:38:16,502
We agreed to renegotiate

485
00:38:16,585 --> 00:38:19,964
the guidelines once again after 2021.

486
00:38:20,881 --> 00:38:22,842
So when that time comes--

487
00:38:22,925 --> 00:38:24,051
Until then,

488
00:38:25,386 --> 00:38:27,346
our kids will grow up
breathing this polluted air.

489
00:38:29,390 --> 00:38:32,476
Are you saying that
you won't agree to this?

490
00:38:32,560 --> 00:38:35,771
The EPA's assessment
on the environmental impact

491
00:38:36,355 --> 00:38:37,565
is wrong.

492
00:38:38,441 --> 00:38:40,818
Are you willing to give up your job

493
00:38:41,402 --> 00:38:43,988
because you won't approve a report?

494
00:38:46,365 --> 00:38:47,533
I'm a scientist, sir.

495
00:38:48,951 --> 00:38:50,328
I believe that nothing

496
00:38:50,411 --> 00:38:52,580
in this world is more valuable than data

497
00:38:53,706 --> 00:38:56,334
applied with responsibility
and interpreted honestly.

498
00:39:00,588 --> 00:39:01,672
Then you leave me no choice.

499
00:39:03,883 --> 00:39:07,178
Secretary Han,
please contact the Korean delegation.

500
00:39:09,930 --> 00:39:12,058
Tell them
I'll be honoring Minister Park's wishes.

501
00:39:14,894 --> 00:39:16,729
He will be held responsible
for today's incident

502
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:18,481
and dismissed from office.

503
00:39:24,945 --> 00:39:27,740
Let them know that
this is my way of showing a long-time ally

504
00:39:27,823 --> 00:39:29,658
my loyalty.

505
00:39:44,340 --> 00:39:45,841
Minister Park.

506
00:40:02,024 --> 00:40:03,442
Is this where I should stand?

507
00:40:03,526 --> 00:40:06,028
SIX MONTHS AGO

508
00:40:06,112 --> 00:40:07,238
Hold on a second.

509
00:40:08,197 --> 00:40:11,575
Something doesn't look right about him.
Don't you agree?

510
00:40:15,746 --> 00:40:17,498
Yes, I see it too.

511
00:40:21,627 --> 00:40:24,171
All right. Let's see.

512
00:40:26,632 --> 00:40:27,883
Let's see.

513
00:40:30,010 --> 00:40:32,721
I think we wear the same size.

514
00:40:34,348 --> 00:40:36,308
Could you bring a pair of shoes
from under my desk?

515
00:40:36,392 --> 00:40:37,435
Yes, sir.

516
00:40:49,071 --> 00:40:50,656
Keep them on even if you don't like them

517
00:40:51,657 --> 00:40:55,286
unless you want
tomorrow's headlines to read,

518
00:40:55,369 --> 00:40:57,830
"Improper Dress Code, Lack of Discipline,

