00:41:15,055 --> 00:41:18,642
you'll have become a true politician.

525
00:41:55,763 --> 00:41:59,350
This is exactly why people at Sejong
call you "Cinderella."

526
00:41:59,558 --> 00:42:02,603
You take your shoes off anywhere.

527
00:42:05,356 --> 00:42:06,857
Seeing how you're here already,

528
00:42:07,483 --> 00:42:09,777
the talk must've gone well. Right?

529
00:42:12,196 --> 00:42:13,405
I'm so relieved.

530
00:42:14,073 --> 00:42:16,158
You have no idea how worried I was.

531
00:42:16,492 --> 00:42:19,370
I may have grown up in a Christian family,

532
00:42:19,453 --> 00:42:21,247
but I prayed for the first time today.

533
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:24,416
Ms. Jeong.

534
00:42:24,792 --> 00:42:26,001
Yes, sir.

535
00:42:27,419 --> 00:42:28,504
Thank you...

536
00:42:32,132 --> 00:42:34,009
for your hard work today.

537
00:43:00,786 --> 00:43:03,664
Look closely. Aren't I right?

538
00:43:03,747 --> 00:43:05,541
It's a global issue.

539
00:43:16,594 --> 00:43:20,514
Let's have some coffee while we work.

540
00:43:21,724 --> 00:43:23,350
-Thank you.
-You must be tired.

541
00:43:27,062 --> 00:43:30,024
-It's a bit difficult to breathe.
-Right?

542
00:43:30,107 --> 00:43:31,734
Let's try this one.

543
00:43:33,027 --> 00:43:35,904
-It has a filter.
-It does.

544
00:43:38,574 --> 00:43:41,535
The filter will keep the fine dust out.

545
00:43:41,619 --> 00:43:43,120
-It'll filter it out.
-Right.

546
00:44:33,045 --> 00:44:36,340
Honey, it's me.
Should I pick you and Si-wan up?

547
00:44:37,633 --> 00:44:38,884
What time do you finish?

548
00:44:43,180 --> 00:44:47,601
THE 100TH ANNIVERSARY
OF THE PROVISIONAL ASSEMBLY OF KOREA

549
00:44:47,685 --> 00:44:50,354
I hear you're boycotting the president's
State of the Nation Address.

550
00:44:50,437 --> 00:44:51,397
Is that true?

551
00:44:51,480 --> 00:44:54,358
Is this your personal opinion
or that of the Seonjin Republican Party?

552
00:44:54,441 --> 00:44:57,528
I hear the president plans to push through
with the peace treaty this year.

553
00:44:57,611 --> 00:45:00,781
Are you against the process of bringing
peace to the Korean Peninsula?

554
00:45:02,908 --> 00:45:04,952
The Seonjin Republican Party and I

555
00:45:05,035 --> 00:45:07,287
are not opposing peace
in the Korean Peninsula.

556
00:45:07,579 --> 00:45:10,916
We are against President Yang's
hasty actions toward North Korea.

557
00:45:11,709 --> 00:45:14,378
President Yang,
who has lost his administrative power

558
00:45:14,461 --> 00:45:17,297
after his approval rates plummeted,
shouldn't use the peace treaty

559
00:45:17,381 --> 00:45:19,758
and unification as a way to
regain his political standing.

560
00:45:19,842 --> 00:45:21,343
Don't you think the cost of unification

561
00:45:21,427 --> 00:45:23,512
is too high for the citizens
if that's the case?

562
00:45:24,513 --> 00:45:25,848
I'd like to advise the president

563
00:45:26,682 --> 00:45:29,351
that the government administration partner
he needs right now

564
00:45:29,435 --> 00:45:31,562
isn't North Korea,
which sits beyond the 38th parallel,

565
00:45:31,645 --> 00:45:32,813
but us, the opposing party.

566
00:45:32,896 --> 00:45:33,772
YUN CHAN-GYEONG

567
00:45:33,856 --> 00:45:34,898
-Shall we go?
-Yes, ma'am.

568
00:45:37,443 --> 00:45:39,194
What is your opinion on the meeting

569
00:45:39,278 --> 00:45:41,739
of the high officials in Panmunjom today?

570
00:45:42,197 --> 00:45:43,741
This is your second boycott.

571
00:45:43,824 --> 00:45:46,326
Doesn't this hinder
resolving matters of public welfare?

572
00:45:47,995 --> 00:45:50,038
-One word, please.
-Ma'am.

573
00:45:52,916 --> 00:45:54,460
That's what I mean.

574
00:45:54,960 --> 00:45:56,628
-The president is here.
-Hello, sir.

575
00:46:07,097 --> 00:46:08,182
THIS ECONOMY IS THE PROBLEM

576
00:46:08,265 --> 00:46:09,641
MOM, WHAT IS UNIFICATION COST?

577
00:46:09,725 --> 00:46:11,310
PEACE SHOULDN'T BE PART OF A DEAL

578
00:46:21,403 --> 00:46:22,237
Hey.

579
00:46:25,240 --> 00:46:27,534
What happened to your face?
Did you get hurt?

580
00:46:27,618 --> 00:46:30,120
Did you get into a fight? Let me see.

581
00:46:32,206 --> 00:46:33,207
Park Si-wan.

582
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:40,798
Slide over.

583
00:46:42,466 --> 00:46:43,300
It's nothing.

584
00:46:43,383 --> 00:46:45,511
It was settled without going to
the advisory board.

585
00:46:52,935 --> 00:46:53,769
What's wrong?

586
00:46:55,729 --> 00:46:58,315
He's only cold towards me. It's unfair.

587
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:02,152
It's karma.

588
00:47:02,694 --> 00:47:06,824
They say how your child treats you
is all karma.

589
00:47:07,449 --> 00:47:09,576
They say it's a reflection

590
00:47:09,660 --> 00:47:11,411
of how good a parent you were.

591
00:47:22,798 --> 00:47:24,591
What is it? Are you upset?

592
00:47:29,721 --> 00:47:30,848
Let's go.

593
00:47:31,431 --> 00:47:33,350
Si-jin is on a field trip. She'll be late.

594
00:47:35,102 --> 00:47:36,937
A field trip? Where to?

595
00:47:37,646 --> 00:47:39,815
Dear honorable citizens,

596
00:47:40,732 --> 00:47:44,444
the Cold War era is now over.

597
00:47:46,113 --> 00:47:49,032
Our country, North Korea,

598
00:47:49,575 --> 00:47:53,203
the US, and China

599
00:47:54,538 --> 00:47:58,292
have declared the end of the war
with North Korea

600
00:47:59,084 --> 00:48:03,171
and have agreed to sign the peace treaty.

601
00:48:06,216 --> 00:48:07,467
-Really?
-Did you know?

602
00:48:07,551 --> 00:48:09,761
They're signing the peace treaty.

603
00:48:10,762 --> 00:48:12,931
Sir, you knew, right?

604
00:48:15,517 --> 00:48:19,271
Don't you think the opposing party will
criticize him more for this hasty policy?

605
00:48:19,354 --> 00:48:21,523
They're not opposing the policy
on North Korea.

606
00:48:23,859 --> 00:48:27,654
They're opposing President Yang Jin-man.

607
00:48:28,238 --> 00:48:29,323
Pardon?

608
00:48:36,997 --> 00:48:39,541
The North Korean working group
is also on their way.

609
00:48:39,625 --> 00:48:41,668
I can't believe this is happening.

610
00:48:42,252 --> 00:48:45,547
Just to be clear, I'm on my way
to Panmunjom as the negotiator

611
00:48:46,131 --> 00:48:47,299
for South Korea, right?

612
00:48:48,091 --> 00:48:51,803
Do you think my face will be included
in the history books in the future?

613
00:48:52,387 --> 00:48:55,933
War, peace, irrevocable reality,

614
00:48:56,975 --> 00:49:00,562
and a future we must protect.

615
00:49:11,156 --> 00:49:13,408
You said Si-jin
went on a field trip today, right?

616
00:49:14,326 --> 00:49:17,454
Should we go pick her up?
Where did you say they went?

617
00:49:17,829 --> 00:49:19,122
The National Assembly.

618
00:49:20,207 --> 00:49:22,501
Oh, yes. That's right.

619
00:49:23,043 --> 00:49:24,252
If there are still those

620
00:49:25,087 --> 00:49:29,508
who fear peace in the Korean Peninsula,

621
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:31,927
I would like you to remember this.

622
00:49:32,761 --> 00:49:38,141
I will fight against you until the end
and gain victory.

623
00:49:40,811 --> 00:49:44,189
This division is a past that needs
to be overcome.

624
00:49:45,357 --> 00:49:47,651
We cannot create a successful future

625
00:49:48,068 --> 00:49:52,948
for the Korean Peninsula or the people
of Korea if this division persists.

626
00:49:54,700 --> 00:49:58,912
We must eliminate hostility
between the North and South.

627
00:50:00,497 --> 00:50:02,332
Our country needs to come together

628
00:50:02,416 --> 00:50:06,420
to obtain peace between the two Koreas.

629
00:50:10,090 --> 00:50:13,885
According to a mutual non-aggression
treaty, the South and the North

630
00:50:14,636 --> 00:50:16,138
declared the end of war.

631
00:50:17,222 --> 00:50:18,807
In addition to the peace treaty,

632
00:50:19,808 --> 00:50:25,439
we have also come to an agreement on
a systematic disarmament.

633
00:50:27,649 --> 00:50:30,527
Therefore, our government will...

634
00:50:41,329 --> 00:50:42,372
Did you get fired?

635
00:50:43,749 --> 00:50:45,542
Fired? Of course not.

636
00:50:58,055 --> 00:50:59,264
Are you okay, Si-wan?

637
00:51:37,302 --> 00:51:39,387
CHANGE IN INTER-KOREAN RELATIONS

638
00:51:42,224 --> 00:51:43,809
-Stop the car.
-Pardon?

639
00:51:43,892 --> 00:51:44,851
Stop the car right now!

640
00:52:00,283 --> 00:52:01,284
Darn it.

641
00:52:02,869 --> 00:52:03,829
Sir.

642
00:52:14,005 --> 00:52:15,674
Would you call the liaison office...

643
00:52:16,591 --> 00:52:18,135
-Yes?
-...in Panmunjom please?

644
00:52:19,052 --> 00:52:20,595
Ask the North Korean working group

645
00:52:22,055 --> 00:52:23,181
for their understanding.

646
00:52:26,017 --> 00:52:27,018
We'll go...

647
00:52:29,521 --> 00:52:30,605
to the Blue House.

648
00:52:40,740 --> 00:52:43,076
-Isn't Mr. Kim there?
-Oh, no!

649
00:52:53,962 --> 00:52:57,424
Next station is Dangsan. Dangsan Station.

650
00:53:08,894 --> 00:53:10,812
Honey. Get up.

651
00:53:13,064 --> 00:53:15,192
Si-jin's teacher
isn't answering her phone.

652
00:53:16,401 --> 00:53:17,861
What about Si-jin?

653
00:53:17,944 --> 00:53:19,613
We have to go get her.

654
00:53:19,696 --> 00:53:21,448
Honey. Si-wan.

655
00:53:39,883 --> 00:53:41,092
Get it together, Su-gyo!

656
00:53:43,345 --> 00:53:45,722
Only focus on what you need to do.

657
00:53:46,806 --> 00:53:47,724
Focus.

658
00:53:48,558 --> 00:53:51,853
Focus on how we can overcome this.

659
00:53:51,937 --> 00:53:52,854
Nothing else.

660
00:53:55,482 --> 00:53:57,192
Do you understand me?

661
00:54:08,370 --> 00:54:09,579
Is this the Security Team?

662
00:54:10,455 --> 00:54:11,581
This is Secretary Han.

663
00:54:13,541 --> 00:54:14,709
How is the president?

664
00:54:23,009 --> 00:54:24,386
We've confirmed the location.

665
00:54:24,511 --> 00:54:25,804
We are on our way.

666
00:54:25,929 --> 00:54:26,930
Let's go!

667
00:54:35,397 --> 00:54:37,232
EXPLOSION AT THE NATIONAL ASSEMBLY

668
00:55:40,462 --> 00:55:41,755
This area is restricted.

669
00:55:42,255 --> 00:55:43,381
My daughter...

670
00:55:43,465 --> 00:55:45,300
My daughter is in there!

671
00:55:45,925 --> 00:55:47,802
-Let me go!
-Please follow police orders!

672
00:55:47,886 --> 00:55:49,387
We can't enter the area!

673
00:55:49,471 --> 00:55:51,389
They're in the same position you are!

674
00:55:55,310 --> 00:55:56,311
Let me in!

675
00:55:56,394 --> 00:55:57,937
Please step away.

676
00:55:58,021 --> 00:55:59,856
-You may not enter.
-Please back up.

677
00:56:00,899 --> 00:56:02,275
Please cooperate.

678
00:56:25,090 --> 00:56:26,341
Goodness.

679
00:56:29,427 --> 00:56:30,387
Si-jin...

680
00:56:32,639 --> 00:56:34,224
Si-jin...

681
00:56:38,645 --> 00:56:40,105
-Si-jin!
-Are you her guardian?

682
00:56:40,188 --> 00:56:41,398
Yes. What happened?

683
00:56:41,481 --> 00:56:43,316
I think she's bleeding
due to external trauma.

684
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:44,943
-Si-jin.
-We must take her to a hospital.

685
00:56:45,026 --> 00:56:46,069
-Si-jin!
-Hold on.

686
00:56:46,569 --> 00:56:48,613
-Please calm down. Take her.
-Si-jin!

687
00:56:48,905 --> 00:56:51,199
-Si-jin!
-Please calm down.

688
00:56:51,282 --> 00:56:52,617
-Si-jin.
-My gosh.

689
00:56:52,700 --> 00:56:55,370
-Is she okay?
-She's okay. She'll be okay.

690
00:56:55,453 --> 00:56:57,497
Only one of you can come with us.
Who will it be?

691
00:56:57,580 --> 00:56:58,957
-I'll go.
-Okay.

692
00:56:59,040 --> 00:57:01,751
Okay. Come in.

693
00:57:01,835 --> 00:57:02,836
Wait there.

694
00:57:02,919 --> 00:57:05,338
-She'll be fine. Don't worry, okay?
-Okay.

695
00:57:26,860 --> 00:57:27,861
Dad.

696
00:57:39,873 --> 00:57:40,999
It's all right.

697
00:57:42,208 --> 00:57:43,751
She'll be fine.

698
00:57:44,210 --> 00:57:45,628
She'll be fine. Don't worry.

699
00:57:45,879 --> 00:57:46,880
Don't worry.

700
00:57:48,381 --> 00:57:49,507
She'll be okay.

701
00:57:50,675 --> 00:57:52,218
Are you Minister Park Mu-jin?

702
00:57:53,428 --> 00:57:54,637
You must come with us, sir.

703
00:57:56,097 --> 00:57:59,267
We've received orders to escort you.
Escort him to the conference room.

704
00:57:59,350 --> 00:58:01,060
-Yes, sir.
-This way, sir.

705
00:58:01,227 --> 00:58:02,145
Let's go.

706
00:58:05,565 --> 00:58:08,026
-Gosh, you're so pretty.
-Are you the same Na-gyeong?

707
00:58:08,610 --> 00:58:10,612
-You look so pretty.
-Totally.

708
00:58:11,488 --> 00:58:13,072
-My gosh.
-It looks great on you.

709
00:58:30,381 --> 00:58:32,467
There was an explosion
at the National Assembly

710
00:58:32,550 --> 00:58:34,969
during the president's
State of the Nation Address.

711
00:58:35,178 --> 00:58:37,388
The main building
of the National Assembly...

712
00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:38,806
EXPLOSION AT THE NATIONAL ASSEMBLY

713
00:58:38,890 --> 00:58:40,558
...has collapsed.

714
00:58:45,563 --> 00:58:48,233
It's me. I can't make it today.

715
00:58:48,942 --> 00:58:50,985
I won't get off work for a while.

716
00:58:51,444 --> 00:58:54,739
I'm disappointed.
I wanted to see you in the dress.

717
00:58:59,077 --> 00:59:01,120
The person you have reached
is not available.

718
00:59:01,204 --> 00:59:02,705
Please leave a message...

719
00:59:10,755 --> 00:59:15,468
I'M ON MY WAY TO THE SCENE.
PLEASE CALL ME.

720
01:00:09,939 --> 01:00:11,232
-Are you done?
-Yes.

721
01:00:12,025 --> 01:00:13,234
HAN NA-GYEONG

722
01:00:13,318 --> 01:00:15,528
I'm Han Na-gyeong
from the NIS Terrorism Task Force.

723
01:00:16,070 --> 01:00:18,281
Lieutenant Lee Jeong-hyeon
from Yeongdeungpo Station.

724
01:00:18,531 --> 01:00:20,491
Please give me a list of all the calls

725
01:00:20,617 --> 01:00:22,869
sent or received through
this base station in the past week.

726
01:00:24,954 --> 01:00:26,122
Yes, ma'am.

727
01:00:26,956 --> 01:00:29,542
First, I'd like to see footage
from all nearby surveillance cameras.

728
01:00:29,626 --> 01:00:32,045
Get me a list of all the vehicles
that passed through the area.

729
01:00:32,128 --> 01:00:33,421
Yes, ma'am.

730
01:00:59,947 --> 01:01:02,200
Hey! Na-gyeong!

731
01:01:05,036 --> 01:01:06,704
JEONG HAN-MO,
NIS TERRORISM TASK FORCE CHIEF

732
01:01:06,788 --> 01:01:09,374
-I'm your superior--
-This is the site of a terrorist attack.

733
01:01:10,041 --> 01:01:12,960
You would’ve been killed
if I had a gun on me right now.

734
01:01:13,044 --> 01:01:16,130
Hey. What have you guys been doing?

735
01:01:17,131 --> 01:01:19,008
While we were running around
in the rain and cold

736
01:01:19,092 --> 01:01:20,551
catching national security violators,

737
01:01:20,677 --> 01:01:23,388
you guys were sitting indoors
and staying warm.

738
01:01:23,471 --> 01:01:25,431
Then shouldn't you at least
earn your keep?

739
01:01:25,515 --> 01:01:28,601
-How could you create this mess?
-I’m trying to earn my keep now.

740
01:01:30,019 --> 01:01:32,105
I'd like for you
to share your list with us.

741
01:01:32,355 --> 01:01:35,316
The list of dissidents, rebels, and spies.

742
01:01:35,400 --> 01:01:36,984
I’d like to compare it with our data

743
01:01:37,068 --> 01:01:38,569
-and classify them as--
-And do what?

744
01:01:38,653 --> 01:01:41,739
Do you think catching the culprit
will change anything at this point?

745
01:01:42,490 --> 01:01:45,702
Attacks? It’s all about prevention.
Nothing else matters.

746
01:01:45,785 --> 01:01:47,453
You're the NIS Terrorism Task Force!

747
01:01:48,413 --> 01:01:49,664
That's what

748
01:01:50,581 --> 01:01:52,041
you guys should’ve done.

749
01:02:10,268 --> 01:02:12,019
-Hurry up!
-It's dangerous. Stay away.

750
01:02:17,608 --> 01:02:18,818
GOING TO THE SCENE. CALL ME.

751
01:02:18,901 --> 01:02:21,195
UNREAD

752
01:02:21,279 --> 01:02:22,613
JUN-O

753
01:02:25,575 --> 01:02:28,161
The person you have reached
is not available.

754
01:02:29,328 --> 01:02:30,413
-It’s me.
-This stop is...

755
01:02:30,496 --> 01:02:32,290
-I can't make it today.
-...the National Assembly.

756
01:02:32,623 --> 01:02:34,667
-I won't get off work for a while.
-National Assembly.

757
01:02:35,084 --> 01:02:36,252
I'm disappointed.

758
01:02:38,379 --> 01:02:41,549
-It's me. I can't make it today.
-This stop is the National Assembly.

759
01:02:41,632 --> 01:02:44,093
-I won't get off work for a while.
-National Assembly.

760
01:02:55,438 --> 01:02:57,482
So the person you’re looking for is...

761
01:03:00,485 --> 01:03:01,486
KIM JUN-O

762
01:03:01,569 --> 01:03:02,945
He works here.

763
01:03:06,032 --> 01:03:07,909
I’m sure he’s not a bombing suspect.

764
01:03:07,992 --> 01:03:10,745
If this is for assistance,
you would've checked with his team.

765
01:03:11,871 --> 01:03:14,457
Knowing you,
the fact that you called from the scene...

766
01:03:14,957 --> 01:03:16,501
KIM JUN-O

767
01:03:16,584 --> 01:03:17,502
Who is this guy?

768
01:03:18,211 --> 01:03:19,462
Please do this for me.

769
01:03:45,029 --> 01:03:46,781
-Go to the presidential residence.
-Okay.

770
01:03:47,615 --> 01:03:49,325
We’ve been waiting for you.

771
01:03:51,869 --> 01:03:54,121
The secretary of the first lady
will take care of your son.

772
01:03:54,205 --> 01:03:55,581
-This way.
-No.

773
01:04:03,130 --> 01:04:05,049
I’ll be attending to you from now on,
Minister Park.

774
01:04:05,341 --> 01:04:06,843
-Wait.
-Please come this way.

775
01:04:12,265 --> 01:04:17,520
YEOMINGWAN 1, YEOMINGWAN 2, YEOMINGWAN 3

776
01:04:17,603 --> 01:04:20,773
Where is the president? Is he okay?

777
01:04:21,274 --> 01:04:24,026
Sir, I just got a call from Chunchugwan.

778
01:04:24,110 --> 01:04:26,737
They asked when the Blue House
will make an official announcement.

779
01:04:26,821 --> 01:04:28,364
Official announcement...

780
01:04:30,366 --> 01:04:33,286
Please tell them to wait.
We need to follow the process.

781
01:04:33,369 --> 01:04:34,704
Just tell them that for now.

782
01:04:37,373 --> 01:04:40,042
Sir, how should we treat those who died
in the attack?

783
01:04:40,126 --> 01:04:42,879
-I think we need someone to guide--
-Haven't the roles been divided yet?

784
01:04:42,962 --> 01:04:44,755
Ask the Minister of Veterans Affairs!

785
01:04:45,381 --> 01:04:46,591
He was...

786
01:04:47,592 --> 01:04:50,219
He was there
in the National Assembly Building today.

787
01:04:52,805 --> 01:04:54,640
Everyone who had the authority to decide

788
01:04:55,308 --> 01:04:58,769
anything regarding the national budget
or regulations were all there.

789
01:05:04,775 --> 01:05:06,277
Tell them to treat the dead...

790
01:05:08,863 --> 01:05:10,531
with the utmost respect permitted.

791
01:05:12,241 --> 01:05:14,493
I’ll report
to the chief presidential secretary.

792
01:05:16,913 --> 01:05:17,914
Yes.

793
01:05:18,331 --> 01:05:20,333
-I'm sorry.
-What are you saying?

794
01:05:20,416 --> 01:05:21,792
-Could you hurry?
-Where is he?

795
01:05:24,795 --> 01:05:26,088
I'm not sure.

796
01:05:26,714 --> 01:05:28,007
Yes. We're checking.

797
01:05:28,090 --> 01:05:31,218
What on earth are you doing right now?

798
01:05:31,302 --> 01:05:32,678
-Hey, come check this out.
-Yes.

799
01:05:33,262 --> 01:05:34,305
Divide this up.

800
01:05:38,768 --> 01:05:41,187
Is the president safe?

801
01:05:42,229 --> 01:05:44,774
Has his safety not been confirmed yet?

802
01:05:44,857 --> 01:05:48,319
-What about the prime minister?
-The president was confirmed dead.

803
01:05:50,655 --> 01:05:51,906
As well as the prime minister,

804
01:05:52,740 --> 01:05:54,200
the speaker of the National Assembly,

805
01:05:54,575 --> 01:05:58,037
the ministers in attendance,
and the cabinet members.

806
01:06:02,208 --> 01:06:04,460
The only survivor
in the line of succession

807
01:06:04,543 --> 01:06:05,836
to the presidency

808
01:06:07,088 --> 01:06:09,215
as dictated by the Constitution is you...

809
01:06:10,716 --> 01:06:12,259
since you weren't in attendance.

810
01:06:52,008 --> 01:06:55,469
Thank you for coming.

811
01:06:56,220 --> 01:06:59,098
They are the presidential secretaries
who will be helping you

812
01:06:59,473 --> 01:07:00,558
from now on.

813
01:07:02,977 --> 01:07:03,936
Hello.

814
01:07:06,439 --> 01:07:09,191
Based on Article 26, Paragraph 1
of the Government Organization Act,

815
01:07:09,775 --> 01:07:10,818
you have been entrusted

816
01:07:11,360 --> 01:07:15,656
with all the authority and duties
of the President of the Republic of Korea.

817
01:07:17,158 --> 01:07:18,034
Pardon?

818
01:07:18,117 --> 01:07:21,954
From this moment forward,
you are now the acting president.

819
01:07:22,038 --> 01:07:24,248
Your term has already begun,
President Park.

820
01:07:31,297 --> 01:07:32,506
We are working on it.

821
01:07:33,215 --> 01:07:34,508
Come help us!

822
01:07:36,302 --> 01:07:38,929
-Did you find him?
-Yes. I located his cell phone.

823
01:07:43,851 --> 01:07:44,769
Where...

824
01:07:46,479 --> 01:07:47,938
Where is he right now?

825
01:07:48,022 --> 01:07:50,399
I’ll send you the link
that shows his current location.

826
01:07:50,483 --> 01:07:51,942
SENDING

827
01:08:04,038 --> 01:08:06,791
THE NATIONAL ASSEMBLY

828
01:08:24,725 --> 01:08:27,937
EXPLOSIVE ORDNANCE DISPOSAL TEAM

829
01:08:33,275 --> 01:08:35,486
It’s a bomb! I found an explosive!

830
01:08:40,533 --> 01:08:41,909
Please evacuate! It’s a bomb!

831
01:08:41,992 --> 01:08:44,787
Please back away! A bomb has been found!

832
01:08:44,954 --> 01:08:47,123
-Please evacuate!
-Evacuate the area!

833
01:08:47,248 --> 01:08:48,791
-This way.
-Please evacuate.

834
01:08:48,958 --> 01:08:51,752
-Hurry up.
-Evacuate everyone here.

835
01:08:52,837 --> 01:08:56,132
We fear there might be a second explosion.
Yes, sir.

836
01:09:08,018 --> 01:09:10,729
You'll be the acting president for 60 days

837
01:09:10,813 --> 01:09:12,523
until the next presidential election.

838
01:09:12,940 --> 01:09:15,192
We'll do our best to prepare

839
01:09:15,276 --> 01:09:18,237
your statement to the nation
as quickly as possible.

840
01:09:18,821 --> 01:09:20,865
-Hey, wait. I'm--
-First,

841
01:09:22,658 --> 01:09:24,368
you need to deal with urgent matters.

842
01:09:26,912 --> 01:09:29,039
It’s a declaration of martial law.

843
01:09:29,707 --> 01:09:30,624
Please sign it.

844
01:09:32,918 --> 01:09:35,087
DECLARATION OF MARTIAL LAW

845
01:09:36,213 --> 01:09:38,799
SIGNATURE OF THE ACTING PRESIDENT

846
01:09:43,679 --> 01:09:45,598
By martial law, do you mean...

847
01:09:45,681 --> 01:09:46,849
This is

848
01:09:47,933 --> 01:09:50,394
a state of national emergency
similar to a time of war.

849
01:09:51,103 --> 01:09:53,564
When we can't secure public order
with the police force alone,

850
01:09:53,647 --> 01:09:56,025
the president,
who is the commander-in-chief,

851
01:09:56,525 --> 01:09:58,319
declares martial law.

852
01:10:01,947 --> 01:10:05,951
Right now,
the commander-in-chief of this country

853
01:10:07,703 --> 01:10:08,746
is you, sir.

854
01:10:31,602 --> 01:10:33,729
DECLARATION OF MARTIAL LAW

855
01:10:36,607 --> 01:10:38,609
SIGNATURE OF THE ACTING PRESIDENT

856
01:10:40,819 --> 01:10:41,695
Now,

857
01:10:44,031 --> 01:10:45,991
you just completed
your first official matter

858
01:10:46,825 --> 01:10:48,869
as acting president, President Park.

859
01:10:50,746 --> 01:10:51,789
This way, sir.

860
01:10:52,289 --> 01:10:53,540
Okay.

861
01:10:58,462 --> 01:11:01,298
Everyone’s waiting for you to arrive.

862
01:11:04,802 --> 01:11:07,972
We have no time to talk about
what measures we should take right now!

863
01:11:08,055 --> 01:11:10,724
We’re at war right now!
Do you not know what that means?

864
01:11:10,808 --> 01:11:12,893
We shouldn’t react emotionally.

865
01:11:13,477 --> 01:11:15,271
We need to figure out what happened first.

866
01:11:15,354 --> 01:11:18,190
It’s too soon to call it a war
and make rash judgments.

867
01:11:19,984 --> 01:11:21,610
CURRENT STATUS OF YEOUIDO

868
01:11:21,694 --> 01:11:23,028
KEY FACILITIES IN NORTH KOREA

869
01:11:23,112 --> 01:11:24,738
KEY FACILITIES IN SOUTH KOREA

870
01:12:09,658 --> 01:12:11,952
He has only six months
of experience in politics,

871
01:12:12,036 --> 01:12:13,787
and all he did was
measure fine dust levels.

872
01:12:13,871 --> 01:12:17,041
-What could he possibly do?
-I'm more afraid he might do something.

873
01:12:17,541 --> 01:12:20,919
That position doesn’t require someone
who will be a hero

874
01:12:21,003 --> 01:12:22,671
and save the world by some fluke.

875
01:12:23,255 --> 01:12:26,216
Sir. We have a problem.

876
01:12:26,342 --> 01:12:28,385
Are you insisting on waging a war
on the Korean Peninsula?

877
01:12:28,677 --> 01:12:30,346
We don’t have time, President Park.

878
01:12:30,637 --> 01:12:33,140
Give your consent to announce DEFCON Two.

